-- allium: 3
-- specs/composition/mtp_fused_x_n_stream.allium
--
-- Scope: the COMPOSITION contract between MTP fused decoding and the
-- n_stream > 1 per-stream KV layout. Specifically: how the Phase 37
-- #5 chain-residual REUSE branch (the "fused decode reads its seed
-- from a prior cycle's chain residual without a host bounce") behaves
-- when more than one server slot drafts MTP fused chains under the
-- per-stream KV layout introduced by
-- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium.
--
-- Why this spec exists: the chain-residual reuse path is the
-- load-bearing perf win of Phase 37/38 — it eliminates a per-cycle
-- D2H+H2D copy of the residual seed. At n_stream == 1 (current
-- production geometry) the path is well-tested. At n_stream > 1 the
-- chain residuals live on a SHARED per-decoder buffer
-- (lctx.default_decoder.mtp_persist[8], indexed by step) with no
-- per-slot/per-stream axis. The persist[] copy is performed at the
-- end of every fused decode; the next fused decode reads from it via
-- the single shared `pending_chain_residual_step` arming field. If
-- slot 0's fused decode arms step k and slot 1 then runs a fused
-- decode before slot 0 reads back, the persist[] buffer holds slot
-- 1's chain — slot 0's read would alias a wrong stream. This is the
-- MTP analogue of Bug C at the residual-seed boundary.
--
-- The composition is INTENTIONALLY HONOURED ON HEAD by an explicit
-- opt-out: common_speculative_draft_batched at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3427-3430 SKIPS
-- the chain-residual arm in the multi-slot batched path, with the
-- inline comment "chain-residual seed is single-slot only (uses one
-- device buffer + one chain)". The env gate
-- LLAMA_MTP_CHAIN_RESIDUAL_SEED defaults OFF; the opt-out is a hard
-- structural decision in the batched dispatch path, not a runtime
-- flag check. This spec binds that decision so a future server-CLI
-- refactor cannot silently re-enable the chain-residual arm under
-- multi-slot dispatch without first making the persist[] buffer
-- per-stream.
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entities for the MTP fused decoder's per-context
--     state (FusedDecoderState, ChainResidualPersistBuffer,
--     ChainResidualArm) and the per-slot scheduler state
--     (SlotChainResidualState) that arms it.
--   - Contracts: MTPFusedReuseSurvivesStreamPatching (the
--     composition-with-Tier-2 argument), MTPChainResidualPerStream
--     (the post-fix contract — the persist buffer becomes
--     [n_embd, n_steps, n_stream]), BatchedMTPSharedDecoderInvariant
--     (the post-D9.5 shared-ctx_tgt model that makes
--     per-stream indexing necessary), MTPFusedAtN_StreamLessThan2Or1
--     (the HONOURED-ON-HEAD opt-out contract), NoCrossStreamChain-
--     Poisoning (the safety property the per-stream fix must
--     preserve).
--   - System-wide invariants binding the per-decoder buffer
--     ownership, the multi-slot opt-out, and the composition
--     argument with Tier 2 read-view patching and Tier 3 unified
--     dispatch.
--   - Open questions for the post-fix per-stream indexing layout
--     and the timing of the lift.
--
-- Excludes:
--   - The FUSED DRAFT GRAPH itself (one ggml_graph_compute produces
--     N drafts + N KV writes). Owned by mtp_fused_draft.allium
--     (FusedDraftStep contract; KvWrittenAtPositionsPThroughPPlusN,
--     FusedDraftRespectsStreamPartition invariants). THIS spec does
--     NOT re-state those contracts — it composes on top of them.
--   - The Tier-2 read-view per-stream patching itself. Owned by
--     specs/kv-cache/per_stream_read_view_patching.allium. THIS
--     spec asserts ONLY that Tier 2's update_cache_copies extension
--     does NOT TOUCH the MTP chain-residual buffer (the buffer is
--     not a K/V read view).
--   - The Tier-3 unified-dispatch surface. Owned by
--     specs/dispatch/unified_stream_dispatch.allium. THIS spec
--     cross-references the unified dispatch invariants in the
--     "post-fix" surface but does NOT bind on Tier 3 landing.
--   - The per-stream KV layout itself (StreamPartition,
--     PerStreamAllocator). Owned by
--     specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium.
--   - The batch composition (chunked-prefill admission shape under
--     Tier 4). Owned by specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium;
--     THIS spec's contracts MUST NOT VIOLATE the redefined
--     BatchCompositionInvariant (TokenBudgetPerUbatch +
--     per-token flag exclusivity). MTP fused decode admits
--     decode-only tokens, which is one valid shape under the
--     chunked-prefill admission contract.

-- ============================================================
-- External entities — per-context fused-decoder state
-- ============================================================

-- The MTP fused decoder's per-llama_context state. One per
-- llama_context (lctx.default_decoder). Carries the chain-residual
-- persist buffer plus the single shared arming field that
-- prepare_mtp_graph_inputs reads. Mirrors the relevant fields of
-- lctx.default_decoder declared in
-- ik_llama.cpp/src/llama-context.h around the default_decoder struct
-- (the persist buffer + pending_chain_residual_step both live as
-- direct fields of that struct).
external entity FusedDecoderState {
    -- The maximum number of chain steps the persist buffer can hold.
    -- Hard-coded to 8 at the allocation site
    -- (ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:6089 — "for (int _k = 0; _k < 8;
    -- ++_k)" + the parallel ggml_tensor_overhead() * 8 allocation).
    persist_capacity_steps: Integer

    -- The number of persist slots populated by the most recent fused
    -- compute. Set at the end of llama_decode_internal's chain-
    -- residual capture block (ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:6130:
    -- "lctx.default_decoder.mtp_persist_n = captured"). Read by
    -- prepare_mtp_graph_inputs at src/llama.cpp:5224 as the upper
    -- bound on the readable step.
    persist_populated_steps: Integer

    -- The single shared arming field. Set per-decode by the SERVER
    -- (via llama_set_draft_input_chain_residual at server-context.cpp:
    -- 3376); read AND cleared by prepare_mtp_graph_inputs at
    -- src/llama.cpp:5222-5223. There is NO per-slot or per-stream
    -- partition of this field at HEAD; the contract surface here
    -- names the property explicitly so the per-stream extension
    -- target is unambiguous.
    pending_chain_residual_step: Integer
}

-- The chain-residual persist buffer itself. Stored as 8 separate
-- ggml_tensor_2d allocations of shape [n_embd, 1] on a
-- ggml_backend_buffer owned by FusedDecoderState.mtp_persist_ctx.
-- At HEAD the buffer dimensionality is one-tensor-per-step with NO
-- stream axis. The post-fix contract MTPChainResidualPerStream below
-- describes the target shape with the additional n_stream axis.
external entity ChainResidualPersistBuffer {
    -- Equal to FusedDecoderState.persist_capacity_steps. Modelled as
    -- a separate entity field so the per-stream extension target can
    -- reference the buffer's dimensionality independently of the
    -- decoder's bookkeeping.
    n_steps: Integer

    -- The n_stream axis. At HEAD this value is 1 by construction
    -- (one buffer per llama_context, no per-stream slab). The
    -- post-fix target is n_stream = max_streams.
    n_stream: Integer

    -- The embedding dimension; the n_embd row of one chain residual.
    -- Matches lctx.model.hparams.n_embd at allocation time
    -- (src/llama.cpp:6088).
    n_embd: Integer
}

-- One slot's chain-residual arming bookkeeping. Lives at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:4322 (the post-
-- accept "slot.mtp_next_chain_residual_step = ..." assignment) and is
-- consumed at server-context.cpp:3375 (the single-slot dispatch
-- branch). The per-slot field exists at HEAD; what is MISSING at
-- HEAD is its propagation to the persist buffer at multi-slot
-- batched dispatch (the multi-slot branch SKIPS it).
external entity SlotChainResidualState {
    slot_id: Integer
    seq_id: Integer

    -- The step index armed for the NEXT fused decode this slot
    -- issues. -1 when no arm is in effect (the host-bounce path
    -- supplies the seed instead). Per
    -- server-context.cpp:4289 ("slot.mtp_next_chain_residual_step =
    -- -1") and :4322 ("slot.mtp_next_chain_residual_step =
    -- (int32_t) ids.size() - 1"). The lifecycle is described
    -- prose-only in the @invariant clauses; transitions are not
    -- modelled here.
    next_chain_residual_step: Integer

    -- True iff this slot is currently running an MTP fused chain
    -- this tick. Used by the multi-slot batched-dispatch invariants
    -- to scope the opt-out.
    in_fused_chain_this_tick: Boolean
}

-- One server tick that contains AT LEAST ONE fused MTP draft.
-- Mirrors the Tick entity in
-- specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium and
-- specs/dispatch/unified_stream_dispatch.allium; redeclared external
-- for self-containment.
external entity Tick {
    index: Integer
    n_active_mtp_slots: Integer
}

-- One stream as observed by the n_stream-aware KV layout. Mirrors
-- Stream in specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium; redeclared
-- external so this spec's contracts are self-contained.
external entity Stream {
    stream_id: Integer
}

-- ============================================================
-- Enumerations
-- ============================================================

-- The chain-residual arming MODE in force for a given dispatch.
-- Names the structural distinction between the single-slot
-- fast path (arm is honoured) and the multi-slot batched path
-- (arm is structurally skipped per server-context.cpp:3427-3430).
enum ChainResidualArmingMode {
    armed_single_slot              -- single-slot dispatch + arm in effect
    skipped_multi_slot             -- multi-slot batched dispatch; arm dropped
    not_armed                      -- single-slot but no arm pending (-1)
}

-- ============================================================
-- Config
-- ============================================================

config {
    -- Maximum streams. Mirrors max_streams in
    -- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium and
    -- specs/dispatch/unified_stream_dispatch.allium. Pinned here so
    -- the post-fix per-stream-indexing contract can reference a
    -- numeric bound without cross-spec navigation.
    max_streams: Integer = 8

    -- The persist buffer's hard-coded step capacity. Equals the
    -- literal 8 at the allocation site
    -- (ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:6089). Pinned here so the
    -- per-stream extension's buffer-size invariant has a numeric
    -- bound to reason about.
    persist_capacity_steps: Integer = 8
}

-- ============================================================
-- Contracts
-- ============================================================

-- The MTPFusedReuseSurvivesStreamPatching — the composition claim
-- between Tier 2's per-stream read-view patching and the MTP fused
-- decoder's chain-residual reuse. Lives at the intersection of
-- ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:5222 (the persist[] read site) and
-- ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:630-749 (update_cache_copies, the Tier
-- 2 extension target). The contract clauses bind that Tier 2's
-- read-view patching does NOT TOUCH the persist buffer; the two
-- mechanisms are independent.
contract MTPFusedReuseSurvivesStreamPatching {
    invoke: (decoder: FusedDecoderState, persist: ChainResidualPersistBuffer) -> Boolean

    @invariant PersistBufferIsNotAKVReadView
        -- The chain-residual persist buffer (FusedDecoderState.
        -- mtp_persist[k]) is allocated on a separate ggml_context
        -- (mtp_persist_ctx) and a separate ggml_backend_buffer
        -- (mtp_persist_buf) from the K/V cache tensors. The
        -- allocation lives at ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:6077-6109
        -- and is INDEPENDENT of llama_kv_cache_init at
        -- src/llama.cpp:790-1155. Tier 2's update_cache_copies
        -- extension at src/llama.cpp:630-749 iterates K/V tensors
        -- only; the persist buffer is not in its iteration set.

    @invariant PersistBufferNotInReadViewRegistry
        -- The Tier-2 ReadViewRegEntry set described in
        -- specs/kv-cache/per_stream_read_view_patching.allium
        -- contains ONLY the K read view (layer_id, is_k = true) and
        -- the V read view (layer_id, is_k = false) per layer. The
        -- persist buffer is not registered as a ReadViewRegEntry
        -- and is not visited by the Tier-2 patch loop. Cross-
        -- references that spec's
        -- ReadViewPatchedByUpdate.EveryActiveReadViewPatchedPerTick.

    @invariant StreamPatchingObliviousToPersistArming
        -- Tier 2's per-stream patching changes the K/V read views'
        -- data_offset and ne[1] per decode. It does NOT touch
        -- decoder.pending_chain_residual_step or any persist[k]
        -- tensor. The MTP fused decoder's persist-read at
        -- src/llama.cpp:5222-5237 reads the buffer obliviously to
        -- whichever stream's K/V views were just patched; the read
        -- semantics are determined entirely by the
        -- pending_chain_residual_step value the caller armed.

    @guidance
        -- This contract is the load-bearing argument that Tier 2 of
        -- PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md (read-view patching at
        -- n_stream > 1) does not regress the MTP fused chain-
        -- residual reuse path at single-slot. The two mechanisms
        -- live in different allocation pools and different patch
        -- loops; they neither help nor hinder each other.
}

-- The MTPChainResidualPerStream — the POST-FIX contract surface.
-- Describes the persist buffer's shape after the per-stream
-- indexing extension lands. NOT HONOURED ON HEAD; binding only
-- after the persist buffer is widened to a per-stream axis and
-- pending_chain_residual_step is split per slot.
--
-- This contract is included so the load-bearing detail of "what the
-- per-stream extension actually has to do" is named in one place,
-- but it is NOT a Tier-2 or Tier-3 prerequisite. The simpler closure
-- is MTPFusedAtN_StreamLessThan2Or1 below — the multi-slot opt-out
-- is honoured today and the spec binds that decision.
contract MTPChainResidualPerStream {
    invoke: (decoder: FusedDecoderState,
             persist: ChainResidualPersistBuffer,
             stream: Stream) -> Boolean

    @invariant PersistShapeIsNStepsByNStream
        -- After the fix, persist.n_stream equals
        -- config.max_streams (or the live cparams.n_seq_max, with
        -- max_streams as the hard upper bound). The chain-residual
        -- read at src/llama.cpp:5225 takes the form
        -- mtp_persist[stream_id][step] (or equivalently a 2D index
        -- into a single tensor of shape [n_embd, n_steps,
        -- n_stream]). Each slot reads from its own stream's slab.

    @invariant ArmFieldIsPerSlotAtDecoderBoundary
        -- After the fix, FusedDecoderState carries one
        -- pending_chain_residual_step per active stream
        -- (vector<int32_t> indexed by stream_id), not a single
        -- scalar. The single-slot fast path arms
        -- pending_chain_residual_step[s] for stream s only. The
        -- multi-slot batched path arms all active streams' entries
        -- in one shot.

    @invariant ReadIndexFollowsStreamId
        -- prepare_mtp_graph_inputs at src/llama.cpp:5202 reads
        -- pending_chain_residual_step[s] for the stream s
        -- corresponding to the slot whose fused decode is being
        -- prepared. The read clears the per-stream entry (preserves
        -- the "auto-clear on consume" semantics of the HEAD code at
        -- src/llama.cpp:5223). No global state survives the read.

    @invariant CaptureWritesAllActiveStreams
        -- The end-of-fused-compute capture at src/llama.cpp:6112-
        -- 6130 D2D-copies each chain residual to its persist slot.
        -- After the fix, the capture writes the per-stream slab
        -- for the dispatching stream (or all dispatching streams,
        -- in the unified-dispatch Tier 3 form). No cross-stream
        -- writes; the capture is a fan-in equivalent to one
        -- per-stream copy.

    @guidance
        -- NOT honoured on HEAD. This contract describes the target
        -- of a future extension that has NOT been scheduled in
        -- PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md. The simpler closure is the
        -- structural opt-out documented in
        -- MTPFusedAtN_StreamLessThan2Or1 below. This contract is
        -- kept here so the cost of the per-stream extension is
        -- explicit if a future workload demands chain-residual
        -- reuse at n_stream > 1.
}

-- The BatchedMTPSharedDecoderInvariant — the post-D9.5 collapsed-
-- context invariant that all MTP slots share ctx_tgt (and therefore
-- share the single FusedDecoderState). Confirmed at HEAD by
-- common/speculative.cpp:1527-1532 (the all_mtp branch asserts every
-- mtp_states[i]->ctx_tgt equals mtp_states[0]->ctx_tgt before
-- entering batched mode). This shared-decoder model is WHAT MAKES
-- the per-stream indexing necessary: if each slot had its own
-- ctx_tgt and its own decoder, the persist buffer's lack of per-
-- stream axis would not be a problem (each slot would own its own
-- buffer). The shared decoder concentrates the cross-slot aliasing
-- onto one buffer and one arming field.
contract BatchedMTPSharedDecoderInvariant {
    invoke: (decoder: FusedDecoderState, tick: Tick) -> Boolean

    @invariant AllMTPSlotsShareCtxTgt
        -- For any tick with multiple active MTP slots, every slot's
        -- common_speculative_state_mtp.ctx_tgt resolves to the same
        -- llama_context. Confirmed structurally at
        -- common/speculative.cpp:1527-1532: the all_mtp branch
        -- short-circuits to per-slot serial fallback when the
        -- ctx_tgt mismatch is detected. The shared-decoder model
        -- is therefore an INVARIANT of the batched fan-out, not a
        -- best-effort property.

    @invariant SharedDecoderImpliesSharedPersistBuffer
        -- Since the FusedDecoderState lives on
        -- lctx.default_decoder and all MTP slots share lctx, all
        -- MTP slots share the persist buffer and the
        -- pending_chain_residual_step field. The shared decoder is
        -- the structural reason chain_residual indexing without a
        -- stream axis aliases across slots.

    @invariant PerSlotIndexingNeededForCrossSlotIsolation
        -- Per-slot chain-residual READS would, in principle, allow
        -- multiple slots to issue fused decodes within one tick
        -- without aliasing — provided the persist buffer carries a
        -- per-stream axis (per MTPChainResidualPerStream above).
        -- Without that extension, the only safe option is to
        -- structurally skip the arm in batched mode
        -- (MTPFusedAtN_StreamLessThan2Or1).

    @guidance
        -- The shared-ctx_tgt invariant is recent (post-D9.5).
        -- Earlier MTP-multislot architectures used per-slot
        -- ctx_tgt instances; under that model the persist buffer
        -- was implicitly per-slot. The collapse to one ctx_tgt
        -- removed the natural per-slot isolation; the chain-
        -- residual buffer is the leftover global state from before
        -- the collapse. See MEMORY entry
        -- project_mtp_multislot_determinism_investigation_failed
        -- for the broader history.
}

-- The MTPFusedAtN_StreamLessThan2Or1 — the contract that binds the
-- HONOURED-ON-HEAD opt-out. The chain-residual arm is HONOURED in
-- single-slot dispatch and STRUCTURALLY SKIPPED in multi-slot
-- batched dispatch. The opt-out is enforced by the dispatch path's
-- structure (server-context.cpp:3357 if-branch vs :3410 else-branch),
-- not by a runtime flag check.
contract MTPFusedAtN_StreamLessThan2Or1 {
    invoke: (slot_states: Set<SlotChainResidualState>, decoder: FusedDecoderState) -> ChainResidualArmingMode

    @invariant SingleSlotPathHonoursArm
        -- When exactly one slot has SlotChainResidualState.
        -- in_fused_chain_this_tick = true, the dispatch enters the
        -- single-slot branch at server-context.cpp:3357. That
        -- branch reads slot.mtp_next_chain_residual_step at
        -- :3375 and, if non-negative, calls
        -- llama_set_draft_input_chain_residual(hs_ctx, step) at
        -- :3376 — which writes decoder.pending_chain_residual_step.
        -- prepare_mtp_graph_inputs then reads persist[step] at
        -- src/llama.cpp:5224. The arming mode is armed_single_slot
        -- (or not_armed if the slot's step is -1).

    @invariant MultiSlotPathSkipsArmStructurally
        -- When two or more slots have
        -- SlotChainResidualState.in_fused_chain_this_tick = true,
        -- the dispatch enters the multi-slot batched branch at
        -- server-context.cpp:3410. That branch SKIPS the chain-
        -- residual arm entirely (no call to
        -- llama_set_draft_input_chain_residual). The arming mode
        -- is skipped_multi_slot. The decoder's
        -- pending_chain_residual_step retains the value from prior
        -- arms (typically -1 after the previous read auto-cleared
        -- it); prepare_mtp_graph_inputs's bound check at
        -- src/llama.cpp:5224 ("step >= 0 && step <
        -- mtp_persist_n") fails on -1 and the host-bounce path at
        -- src/llama.cpp:5241-5247 supplies the seed instead.

    @invariant EnvGateCannotReintroduceCrossSlotChain
        -- The single-slot chain-residual arm IS gated by
        -- LLAMA_MTP_CHAIN_RESIDUAL_SEED at server-context.cpp:3370-
        -- 3374 (or by LLAMA_MTP_FULL_2). The env gate ONLY
        -- enables the single-slot path; it CANNOT add the arm to
        -- the multi-slot batched path because the call site does
        -- not exist there. A future refactor that moves the env
        -- gate higher (above the if/else branch) and threads it
        -- through both arms would violate this contract.

    @invariant N_StreamOneIsTriviallySafe
        -- When the runtime cparams.n_seq_max == 1 (single-slot
        -- deployment, the current production configuration for
        -- 27B-MTP-IR), only one slot ever exists and the multi-
        -- slot branch is unreachable. The arming mode is always
        -- armed_single_slot or not_armed. Cross-references
        -- PreservesNStream1Production from
        -- specs/kv-cache/per_stream_read_view_patching.allium.

    @guidance
        -- This contract is HONOURED ON HEAD. The RED test in
        -- tests/spec/test-mtp-fused-x-n-stream.cpp (P0.B.S4)
        -- exercises a 2-slot MTP tick and asserts (a)
        -- pending_chain_residual_step is -1 at the entry to
        -- prepare_mtp_graph_inputs, (b) no
        -- llama_set_draft_input_chain_residual call fires from the
        -- batched path. The test PASSES on HEAD; it exists as a
        -- regression guard against a future refactor that moves the
        -- env gate or unifies the dispatch arms.
}

-- The NoCrossStreamChainPoisoning — the SAFETY property the
-- composition guarantees. Equivalent statement: slot S's
-- chain_residual reads never alias slot S' ≠ S's chain_residual
-- writes. This is the MTP analogue of NoCrossStreamLeakage from
-- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium, applied to the persist
-- buffer. The property holds at HEAD by the opt-out
-- (MTPFusedAtN_StreamLessThan2Or1) and would continue to hold under
-- the per-stream extension (MTPChainResidualPerStream).
contract NoCrossStreamChainPoisoning {
    invoke: (slot_states: Set<SlotChainResidualState>, decoder: FusedDecoderState) -> Boolean

    @invariant NoCrossSlotPersistRead
        -- For any two slots S and S' with S != S' and both having
        -- in_fused_chain_this_tick = true, S's fused decode at
        -- src/llama.cpp:5202 (prepare_mtp_graph_inputs) does NOT
        -- read a persist[k] tensor that was written by S''s prior
        -- fused decode. At HEAD this holds because the multi-slot
        -- path does not arm (the persist read short-circuits on
        -- step == -1). Under the per-stream extension this would
        -- hold because the read indexes persist[S][k] and the
        -- prior write was persist[S'][k].

    @invariant NoCrossSlotArmingFieldRace
        -- For any two slots S and S' that issue fused decodes within
        -- one tick, S's arm at server-context.cpp:3376 does NOT
        -- race with S''s read at src/llama.cpp:5222. At HEAD this
        -- holds because the multi-slot path does not call the arm
        -- API at all (the single shared
        -- pending_chain_residual_step is written by neither slot's
        -- dispatch). Under the per-stream extension this would
        -- hold because the arm writes
        -- pending_chain_residual_step[S] and the read reads
        -- pending_chain_residual_step[S'].

    @invariant PersistCaptureWritesDoNotCrossStreams
        -- The end-of-fused-compute capture at
        -- src/llama.cpp:6112-6130 D2D-copies the just-computed
        -- chain_residuals into persist[]. At HEAD the capture
        -- writes the SHARED persist[k] for whichever slot's fused
        -- decode just completed; this is the structural reason
        -- the multi-slot opt-out is necessary. Under the per-stream
        -- extension the capture would write persist[S][k] for the
        -- dispatching stream S; no cross-stream write would occur.

    @invariant SafetyHoldsUnderEitherClosure
        -- The NoCrossSlot properties above hold under EITHER of two
        -- closures: (a) the structural opt-out in batched mode
        -- (HEAD) — the cross-slot read/write path is unreachable;
        -- (b) the per-stream extension — the cross-slot read/write
        -- path is reachable but indexed disjointly. Both closures
        -- satisfy this contract; the choice between them is a
        -- perf/complexity trade-off documented in OQ-1 below.

    @guidance
        -- This contract is the MTP analogue of the Bug C absence
        -- argument. Under (a) the closure is structural (the path
        -- doesn't fire); under (b) it is by-construction (the
        -- indexing partitions the state). Either way the safety
        -- property holds; future workloads at n_stream > 1 will
        -- determine whether (a)'s perf cost (lost reuse) demands
        -- the (b) extension.
}

-- ============================================================
-- Invariants — system-wide
-- ============================================================

-- The persist-buffer-is-per-decoder property. For any FusedDecoderState
-- d, the persist buffer holds at most persist_capacity_steps tensors
-- and has no per-stream axis at HEAD. Lifts
-- MTPChainResidualPerStream.PersistShapeIsNStepsByNStream's HEAD
-- form: at HEAD, n_stream collapses to 1 by construction.
invariant PersistBufferIsPerDecoderAtHead {
    for d in FusedDecoderStates:
        d.persist_capacity_steps = config.persist_capacity_steps
            and d.persist_populated_steps <= d.persist_capacity_steps
}

-- The arming-mode-is-structural property. For every tick that
-- dispatches at least one fused MTP decode, the chain-residual
-- arming mode is either armed_single_slot, not_armed, or
-- skipped_multi_slot. There is no fourth mode. Lifts
-- MTPFusedAtN_StreamLessThan2Or1's structural distinction to a
-- system-wide property.
invariant ArmingModeIsStructural {
    for tick in MTPDispatchTicks:
        ArmingModeAt(tick) in {armed_single_slot, not_armed, skipped_multi_slot}
}

-- The multi-slot-skips-arm property. For every tick with two or
-- more active MTP slots, the arming mode is skipped_multi_slot.
-- Lifts MultiSlotPathSkipsArmStructurally.
invariant MultiSlotImpliesSkippedArm {
    for tick in MTPDispatchTicks:
        tick.n_active_mtp_slots >= 2
            implies ArmingModeAt(tick) = skipped_multi_slot
}

-- The no-cross-slot-poisoning property. For any tick with two or
-- more active MTP slots, no slot's persist read aliases another
-- slot's persist write within the same tick. Lifts
-- NoCrossStreamChainPoisoning.SafetyHoldsUnderEitherClosure.
invariant NoCrossSlotPoisoningSystemWide {
    for tick in MTPDispatchTicks:
        tick.n_active_mtp_slots >= 2
            implies NoSlotReadAliasesAnotherSlotWriteIn(tick)
}

-- The Tier-2 obliviousness property. For every tick that runs
-- update_cache_copies (the Tier-2 patch entry point), the patch
-- iteration does NOT touch the persist buffer or the arming field.
-- Lifts MTPFusedReuseSurvivesStreamPatching.
-- StreamPatchingObliviousToPersistArming.
invariant Tier2PatchObliviousToPersistArming {
    for tick in Ticks:
        Tier2PatchedTensorsAt(tick).disjoint(PersistTensorsOf(DecoderAt(tick)))
            and Tier2PatchedFieldsAt(tick).disjoint(PersistArmingFieldsOf(DecoderAt(tick)))
}

-- The composition-with-Tier-3-unified-dispatch property. Under
-- Tier 3 (specs/dispatch/unified_stream_dispatch.allium), one
-- llama_decode per tick covers all active streams via ne[3]. The
-- fused MTP draft path runs INSIDE that single decode for the
-- streams that have armed fused chains; the chain-residual buffer
-- must be partitioned per stream (per MTPChainResidualPerStream)
-- for the unified dispatch to compose cleanly. Until that extension
-- lands, Tier 3 inherits the HEAD opt-out: multi-stream MTP fused
-- chains run through the host-bounce path.
invariant Tier3UnifiedDispatchInheritsHEADOptOut {
    for tick in UnifiedDispatchTicks:
        tick.n_active_mtp_slots >= 2
            implies ArmingModeAt(tick) = skipped_multi_slot
}

-- ============================================================
-- Open Questions
-- ============================================================

-- OQ-1: When (if ever) does the per-stream extension to the
--   persist buffer land? The trade-off is concrete:
--   (a) HEAD opt-out — chain-residual reuse loses across n_stream > 1
--       multi-slot MTP fused ticks. Perf cost: one D2H+H2D copy of
--       n_embd floats per fused decode per active slot per tick
--       (~0.5 ms at n_embd = 5120 on PCIe 4.0). At n_seq_max = 2
--       and decode tick rate ~30/s, the perf cost is ~30 ms/s of
--       host bounce overhead. Not zero, but small relative to the
--       decode budget.
--   (b) Per-stream extension — persist becomes [n_embd, n_steps,
--       n_stream], pending_chain_residual_step becomes per-stream.
--       Implementation cost: persist_buf allocation grows by
--       n_stream; the capture loop at src/llama.cpp:6112-6130 must
--       index per stream; prepare_mtp_graph_inputs's read must
--       resolve the calling stream's id (currently it has no such
--       parameter). ~200 LOC of disciplined refactor.
--   Resolve when MTP-IR at n_seq_max >= 2 becomes a production
--   target. Current production runs at n_seq_max = 1 so the
--   opt-out cost is zero.
--
-- OQ-2: Does the multi-slot batched path EVER want chain-residual
--   reuse for the FIRST slot in the batch? The single-slot fast
--   path at server-context.cpp:3357 honours the arm because only
--   one slot is dispatching. The multi-slot batched path could
--   honour slot 0's arm and skip slots 1..N-1's. This would recover
--   ~1/N of the perf benefit at multi-slot cost. The current opt-
--   out is N=0; the lift would require pending_chain_residual_step
--   to be aware of WHICH slot's chain its persist[] data represents
--   (or guarantee that slot 0 captured the last fused chain on this
--   decoder). The simpler full per-stream extension (OQ-1)
--   subsumes this; not worth implementing as an intermediate step.
--
-- OQ-3: Is there a structural way to PREVENT a future refactor
--   from accidentally re-enabling chain-residual arming under
--   multi-slot dispatch without first satisfying
--   MTPChainResidualPerStream? Today the opt-out is enforced by
--   the dispatch path's if/else structure. A future unification
--   of the dispatch arms (e.g., one code path that handles
--   N >= 1 uniformly) is exactly what Tier 3 does for the OUTER
--   llama_decode loop. The contracts above bind the property
--   structurally: a unified dispatch arm that calls
--   llama_set_draft_input_chain_residual unconditionally would
--   violate MTPFusedAtN_StreamLessThan2Or1.
--   MultiSlotPathSkipsArmStructurally. The Allium check + the
--   RED test in tests/spec/test-mtp-fused-x-n-stream.cpp would
--   catch the regression at PR time.

-- ============================================================
-- Implementation notes
-- ============================================================

-- Code-side anchors (paths from yarn-agentic root, line numbers
-- verified 2026-05-21 against current HEAD):
--   ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:5202-5267
--     — prepare_mtp_graph_inputs; the chain-residual reuse read
--       at 5222-5238. The READ site for the persist buffer.
--   ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:5222-5223
--     — "const int step = lctx.default_decoder.
--        pending_chain_residual_step;
--        lctx.default_decoder.pending_chain_residual_step = -1;"
--       — the auto-clear semantics. The arming field is read AND
--       cleared by the consume site; the next decode without a
--       fresh arm falls through to the host-bounce path.
--   ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:5224-5237
--     — the persist[step] bound check + tensor copy. "step >= 0
--       && step < lctx.default_decoder.mtp_persist_n" is the only
--       guard against reading stale persist data.
--   ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:6064-6131
--     — the end-of-fused-compute capture block. D2D-copies each
--       chain_residual[k] to persist[k]; updates persist_n.
--   ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:6088-6092
--     — the persist allocation: 8 ggml_new_tensor_2d calls of
--       shape [n_embd, 1]. The "8" is hard-coded;
--       config.persist_capacity_steps mirrors it.
--   ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:5330-5345
--     — the stale-pointer guard. mtp_fused_chain_residuals[]
--       (the sched-owned source tensors) are nulled when the next
--       decode is NOT fused; persist[] is NOT touched here because
--       it lives in a context-owned backend buffer with persist_n
--       as its validity counter.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3215-3346
--     — the per-slot mtp_collected gather loop. Slots add their
--       (slot, input) pair to mtp_collected when ready to draft;
--       the count of mtp_collected drives the single-slot vs
--       multi-slot dispatch branch below.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3350-3409
--     — the single-slot fast path. Reads slot.mtp_next_chain_
--       residual_step at :3375; calls llama_set_draft_input_
--       chain_residual(hs_ctx, step) at :3376 ONLY if the
--       chain-residual env gate is set AND the slot's step is
--       non-negative.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3410-3475
--     — the multi-slot batched path. SKIPS the chain-residual arm
--       entirely; the inline comment at :3427-3430 names the
--       reason ("uses one device buffer + one chain"). Calls
--       llama_set_draft_input_hidden_state_multi at :3426 and
--       common_speculative_draft_batched at :3441.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3370-3374
--     — the LLAMA_MTP_CHAIN_RESIDUAL_SEED + LLAMA_MTP_FULL_2 env
--       gates. Only consulted in the single-slot branch; the
--       multi-slot branch ignores them by construction.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:4289
--     — slot.mtp_next_chain_residual_step = -1 on rejection; the
--       "any_rejected && slot.spec_ckpt.valid" branch resets the
--       arm because mtp_accept_tokens runs an UPDATE_ACCEPTED
--       decode that invalidates the prior fused chain.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:4322
--     — slot.mtp_next_chain_residual_step = ids.size() - 1 on
--       successful accept; arms the next cycle's read at the
--       new last-accepted-position residual index.
--   ik_llama.cpp/common/speculative.cpp:1481-1532
--     — common_speculative_draft_batched; the multi-slot
--       batched primitive. Asserts all slots share ctx_tgt
--       (BatchedMTPSharedDecoderInvariant.AllMTPSlotsShareCtxTgt)
--       at lines 1527-1532. Falls back to per-slot serial if
--       not.
--
-- Black-box helpers used inline in the system-wide invariants
-- (not in `deferred` per project convention — they have no
-- separate .allium spec):
--   FusedDecoderStates, MTPDispatchTicks, Ticks, ArmingModeAt,
--   NoSlotReadAliasesAnotherSlotWriteIn, Tier2PatchedTensorsAt,
--   Tier2PatchedFieldsAt, PersistTensorsOf, PersistArmingFieldsOf,
--   DecoderAt, UnifiedDispatchTicks.
--
-- Test infrastructure to drive from this spec via allium:propagate
-- (P0.B.S4 in PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md):
--   - tests/spec/test-mtp-fused-x-n-stream.cpp
--     * Drives a 2-slot MTP fused tick at n_seq_max = 2; asserts
--       (a) pending_chain_residual_step is -1 at the entry to
--           prepare_mtp_graph_inputs for both slots'
--           fused decodes (the host-bounce path takes over),
--       (b) no llama_set_draft_input_chain_residual call fires
--           from the batched-dispatch path,
--       (c) the per-slot host-bounce hidden states supplied by
--           llama_set_draft_input_hidden_state_multi are consumed
--           correctly (the seed for each slot's fused decode
--           comes from the host path).
--     * EXPECTED TO PASS on HEAD (the opt-out is the HEAD
--       behaviour); the test exists as a regression guard.
--   - tests/spec/test-mtp-fused-x-n-stream-1slot.cpp
--     * Drives a 1-slot MTP fused tick at n_seq_max = 2; asserts
--       (a) the single-slot path arms
--           pending_chain_residual_step when
--           LLAMA_MTP_CHAIN_RESIDUAL_SEED is set,
--       (b) prepare_mtp_graph_inputs reads persist[step] and the
--           seed matches expectation.
--     * EXPECTED TO PASS on HEAD. Together with the 2-slot test,
--       binds the structural distinction between the two paths.

-- ============================================================
-- Related specs
-- ============================================================

-- mtp_fused_draft.allium (at repo root, not under specs/)
--   The abstract FusedDraftStep contract. THIS spec composes on
--   top of mtp_fused_draft.allium's FusedDraftStep: the persist
--   buffer described here is the implementation mechanism that
--   the Phase 37 #5 reuse branch uses to elide one host bounce
--   per fused round. mtp_fused_draft.allium's
--   FusedDraftRespectsStreamPartition asserts the FUSED GRAPH's
--   KV writes are stream-local; THIS spec asserts the
--   chain-residual-reuse PATH is stream-safe (under the opt-out
--   or per-stream extension).
--
-- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium
--   The 4D per-stream KV layout. PerStreamAllocator,
--   StreamPartition, NoCrossStreamLeakage live there. THIS spec's
--   NoCrossStreamChainPoisoning is the MTP analogue of
--   NoCrossStreamLeakage applied to the persist buffer.
--
-- specs/kv-cache/per_stream_read_view_patching.allium
--   The Tier-2 read-view patching contract. THIS spec asserts
--   (via MTPFusedReuseSurvivesStreamPatching) that Tier 2's
--   update_cache_copies extension does NOT touch the persist
--   buffer or the arming field — the two mechanisms are in
--   different allocation pools and different patch loops.
--
-- specs/dispatch/unified_stream_dispatch.allium
--   The Tier-3 unified-dispatch contract. Cross-referenced by
--   Tier3UnifiedDispatchInheritsHEADOptOut: Tier 3 does NOT lift
--   the multi-slot opt-out; multi-stream MTP fused chains
--   continue to run through the host-bounce path until the
--   per-stream extension (MTPChainResidualPerStream) lands.
--
-- specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium
--   The scheduler-level admission contracts (chunked-prefill
--   admission under Tier 4). THIS spec's contracts must NOT
--   violate the redefined BatchCompositionInvariant
--   (TokenBudgetPerUbatch + per-token flag exclusivity). The
--   MTP fused decode contributes is_decode tokens per
--   DecodePriorityAdmission (per mtp_fused_draft.allium's
--   FusedDraftRoundsRunOnPureDecodeBatches); THIS spec's
--   multi-slot opt-out does not alter that property.
--
-- specs/dflash/dflash_server_cli.allium
--   The DFlash multi-slot server-CLI contract. DFlash and MTP
--   are alternative spec backends sharing the
--   common_speculative_draft_batched dispatcher. The two coexist
--   in common/speculative.cpp:1481-1574: the function tries
--   all-MTP first, falls back to all-DFlash, then to per-slot
--   serial. THIS spec binds the all-MTP branch; the all-DFlash
--   branch is owned by dflash_server_cli.allium.
